{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>Project Overview</h2>\n<p>In late 2018, we made improvements to how we get maps on <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/\">boston.gov</a>. The product goals were to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fully integrate with Drupal, boston.gov's CMS</li>\n<li>Fit the <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/departments/innovation-and-technology/brand-guidelines\">city's brand</a></li>\n<li>Integrate with the infrastructure our Analytics Team uses to share data (ArcGIS Online)</li>\n<li>Be easy to update</li>\n<li>Be mobile reponsive and nice to use</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We built a custom Drupal component so maps could be placed on any page and leveraged hosted data sources maintained by our data team. We wrote more about these updates on the Digital Team's blog: <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/news/building-better-maps-bostongov\">Building better maps for boston.gov</a>.</p>\n<h2>Tech</h2>\n<p>From a technical stand point, we leveraged <a href=\"https://github.com/CityOfBoston/patterns/tree/develop/web-components/map\">web components</a> that we wrapped up in a custom Drupal component. The web component uses <a href=\"https://esri.github.io/esri-leaflet/\">esri-leafet</a> which lets us integrate with our data hosted on <a href=\"http://boston.maps.arcgis.com/home/index.html\">ArcGIS Online</a>.</p>\n<h2>Quicklinks</h2>\n<hr>\n<div class=\"imageBlock\">\n    <div>\n        <a href=\"https://www.boston.gov/news/building-better-maps-bostongov\">\n            <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 900px;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 54.93741307371349%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"Building better maps for boston.gov\" title src=\"/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/48396/maps-blog-post.png\" srcset=\"/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/39d7a/maps-blog-post.png 225w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/d45f3/maps-blog-post.png 450w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/48396/maps-blog-post.png 900w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/14262/maps-blog-post.png 1350w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/c1e46/maps-blog-post.png 1800w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/83e3a/maps-blog-post.png 2700w,\n/static/d481080261343e71bfbe0b704a96a931/4bafc/maps-blog-post.png 2876w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\">\n  </span>\n        </a>\n    </div>\n</div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Maps on boston.gov","myRole":"Product Manager"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/maps-boston-gov/"}}